4. Create an amount of test files to check the implementation of mymalloc() and myfree()
    -Explain the test files in Program Descriptions
5. Lastly create the Makefile
    -Use the slides from lecture and recitation to help

---Program Descriptions---
I created 5 individual test programs to test the correctness of mymalloc() and myfree().
1. overlaptest
    -The code will allocate 2 object a1 and a2. Using the memset function, it fills each object that the distinct byte pattern. Lastly, it'll check if each object will contain the written pattern and more importantly if the data overlapped. If the test reports that the memory did overlap, I wiil have to adjust mymalloc and myfree code.
2. leaktest
    -This will detected a leak. This test is supposed to return the leak detection. This test WILL output an error to make sure that the leak detection is functional.
3. errortest
    -This test was an example I pulled from the assignment writeup. The test WILL return an invalid pointer.
4. freetest
    -This test is NOT supposed to fail. This test is strictly made to check if myfree() is marking the blocks correctly. It should output "Free() works correctly."
5. coalescetest
    -This test is NOT supposed to fail. This test will check if coalescing function works. This should output "Coalescing works!"
---Extra Notes---
All allocations are rounded up to the nearest multiple of 8
Leak detector cannot call exit()
No metadata is stored inside payloads
